[SN]TITLE[SN]
'Sudden death' reported on farm near Downpatrick

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An investigation has begun into the death of a man in his 70s on a farm in County Down.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident, thought to have involved a tractor, happened at Kilclief, between Ardglass and Strangford, at about 17:30 GMT on Monday.
The victim has been named locally as Pat Curran.
The Health and Safety Executive (HSENI), which deals with work-related accidents, has begun an investigation.
A HSENI spokesperson said: "Our thoughts are with the man's family at this most difficult time."
SDLP MP Margaret Ritchie said he was well known in the area.
"He's been involved in farming all his life, highly respected in the local community by his peers, neighbours, friends and relatives," she said.
